    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Commiphora leptophloeos are its antimicrobial activity, which is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and saponins, allowing it to inhibit the growth of various microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi. The plant's antioxidant properties are also notable, with volatile oils and phenolic compounds exhibiting strong free radical scavenging activity and reducing oxidative stress in cells. Commiphora leptophloeos has anti-inflammatory properties, attributed to the action of sesquiterpenes and diterpenes, which inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines, leading to reduced inflammation. The plant's antifungal activity is primarily due to the presence of terpenoids, which have been shown to inhibit the growth of various fungal species, including Candida and Aspergillus. Additionally, Commiphora leptophloeos has analgesic properties, with bioactive compounds such as alkaloids and glycosides exhibiting pain-relieving effects by inhibiting the production of pain-causing neurotransmitters.",
