    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Commiphora leptophloeos are commiphora oil, commiphora tincture, commiphora salve, and resin extract. Commiphora oil is obtained through steam distillation of the plant's gum resin, containing 50-70% alpha-pinene, beta-pinene, and caryophyllene. Commiphora tincture is a liquid extract prepared by soaking the plant's resin in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin, typically containing 10-20% resin. Commiphora salve is a topical preparation made by infusing the plant's resin in a carrier oil, often used to treat skin issues and wounds. Resin extract, typically in powder form, is obtained through drying and grinding the plant's resin, often used as a natural remedy for various health issues due to its anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties.",
